<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-22T13:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-22T13:54:00-05:00" n="776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/188: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-22T22:00:00+03:06">June
                                        22, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 10:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>175. Acting Foreign Minister today amplified statements reported in
                                Cairo’s 1670, June 18, 10 a.m. stating that deaths by starvation are
                                occurring in southern Hejaz and that besides stopping free
                                distribution of food Saudi Government has suspended sales because of
                                depleted stocks. He produced figures to show that present Government
                                stocks of foodstuffs now total 2,105 tons only, of which 1,363 are
                                for general distribution.</p>
                            <p>American representative in MESC<note n="14" xml:id="d776fn14">Middle
                                    East Supply Center.</note> has been asked to supply Legation
                                with statistics of food imported in 1943 and current year to aid in
                                evaluating figures of Acting Minister.</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <p>Statistics by airmail tomorrow.<note n="15" xml:id="d776fn15">Forwarded from Jidda in despatch 193, June 22.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>